result.execSummary:
The defendant William P Janes was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Controlled Substance, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:21 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Jon Wilsnack.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  DA recites agreement - defendant will plea to count 3 and count 4 amended to Misdemeanor Bail jumping on 2015CF22, count 1 on 2015CM55 and count 1 on 2015CM20 with probation.  Atty Wilsnack concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 3 and count 4 as amended on 2015CF22 and orders counts 1 & 2 be dismissed and read-in, finds the defendant guilty on count 1 on 2015CM55, and finds the defendant guilty on count 1 on 2015CM20 and orders count 2 be dismissed and read-in.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Wilsnack.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

2015CM20 - 30 days county jail, stayed and places the defendant on probation for 2 years.
2015CF22(count 3 & 4) - SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 2 years.
2015CM55 - 9 months county jail, stayed and places the defendant on probation for 2 years.

CONDITIONS (ALL COUNTS):

-Court costs.
-Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
-Defendant is to complete an alcohol and drug abuse assessment (AODA) and comply with any follow-up counseling as recommended.
-2015CM55 - Restitution of $360.00 Jt & Several
-2015CF22 - Restitution of $280.57
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.
